-- Sri Lanka Defeats Australia by Seven Wickets in Twenty20 Cricket Match
-- B y   J a m e s   C o n e
-- 2010-10-31T12:55:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-31/sri-lanka-defeats-australia-by-seven-wickets-in-twenty20-cricket-match.html
Captain Kumar Sangakkara scored an
unbeaten 44 as Sri Lanka beat Australia by seven wickets in a
Twenty20 cricket international in Perth today.  Sangakkara top-scored in the visitors’ reply, while
Tillakaratne Dilshan hit 41 as Sri Lanka reached its victory
target with 21 balls remaining. Thisara Perera finished off the
match by striking a six, a four, then another six off successive
balls.  Australia was restricted to 43-5, before recovering to
reach 133-8 from its 20 overs. A 71-run third-wicket partnership
put Sri Lanka on course to win, with Perera’s late burst taking
the team to 135-3. He ended on 17 from only four balls.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Cone at 
 jcone@bloomberg.net  